abstract: When the plane with the weary Yankee team, unhappy after its second consecutive playoff defeat in Kansas City, landed in Newark shortly after 4 A.M. on Friday, a 70-year-old member of the club broke away from the others.

HOUSTON, Oct. 11--In a four-hour game spiced with disputed plays, the Philadelphia Phillies rallied twice today to defeat the Houston Astros, 5-3, in 10 innings and deadlock the playoff for the National League pennant at 2-2. The deciding game is here tomorrow night.
headline_main: Phils Turn Back Astros in 10th, 5-3, and Tie Playoff at 2-2; Luzinski Pinch Double Key Blow Strange Happenings on Field Astros Take 2-0 Lead Phillies Win, 5-3, In 10th Pujols Triples to Center Trillo Drives In Rose

abstract: PHILADELPHIA, Oct. 7 The Philadelphia Phillies, shooting for their first pennant in 30 years, won the opening game of the National League playoff tonight when they defeated the Houston Astros, 3-1, on a two-run homer by Greg Luzinski.
